cs.LO, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.PL, cs.DS

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper proposes a probabilistic temporal logic to express quantitative properties of the models.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper proposes techniques to synthesize a controller for the model which makes the property true.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper deals with control of real-time systems.
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is relevant as the paper proposes an extension of probabilistic timed automata to model partially observable systems.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is less likely but still possible as the paper proposes an approach based on an integer discretization and a grid-based abstraction, which involves algorithmic techniques.
